It is possible that you may be suffering from conjunctivitis, which is an inflammation of the conjunctiva, the thin, transparent membrane that covers the white part of the eye and the inner surface of the eyelids. Treatment for conjunctivitis typically involves the use of artificial tears, cold compresses, and anti-inflammatory medications.
